addictive.Name: addictive
addictive.Description: producing or tending to cause addiction.

antithetical.Name: antithetical
antithetical.Description: directly opposed or contrasted; mutually incompatible.

bloodlusted.Name: bloodlusted
bloodlusted.Description: Bloodlust is when a character will begin a fight with their most powerful means of destroying an enemy as quickly and efficiently as possible without morals, or any other character trait that might hold them back, getting in the way.

bold.Name: bold
bold.Description: not hesitating or fearful in the face of actual or possible danger or rebuff; courageous and daring.

efficient.Name: efficient
efficient.Description: performing or functioning in the best possible manner with the least waste of time and effort; having and using requisite knowledge, skill, and industry; competent; capable.

effluvial.Name: effluvial
effluvial.Description: being a slight or invisible exhalation or vapor, especially one that is disagreeable or noxious.

energetic.Name: energetic
energetic.Description: possessing or exhibiting energy, especially in abundance; vigorous.

expert.Name: expert
expert.Description: possessing special skill or knowledge; trained by practice; skillful or skilled (often followed by in or at).

heroic.Name: heroic
heroic.Description: of, relating to, or characteristic of a hero or heroine.

homeopathic.Name: homeopathic
homeopathic.Description: of, relating to, or according to the principles of homeopathy. Homeopathy is the method of treating disease by drugs, given in minute doses, that would produce in a healthy person symptoms similar to those of the disease (opposed to allopathy).

homicidal.Name: homicidal
homicidal.Description: having a tendency to commit homicide. Homicide is the killing of one human being by another.

imposing.Name: imposing
imposing.Description: very impressive because of great size, stately appearance, dignity, elegance, etc.

impressive.Name: impressive
impressive.Description: having the ability to impress the mind; arousing admiration, awe, respect, etc.; moving; admirable.

inspiring.Name: inspiring
inspiring.Description: to be able to fill others with an animating, quickening, or exalting influence.

jaded.Name: jaded
jaded.Description: worn out or wearied, as by overwork or overuse.

lust-lusted.Name: lust-lusted
lust-lusted.Description: Lust-lusted is when a character will begin a fight with their most powerful means of destroying an enemy as quickly and efficiently as possible without morals, or any other character trait that might hold them back, getting in the way, with the objective of inducing lust in the enemy.

mad.Name: mad
mad.Description: enraged; greatly provoked or irritated; angry.

mass-murdering.Name: mass-murdering
mass-murdering.Description: someone who commits many mass murders.

millenial.Name: millenial
millenial.Description: a person born in the 1980s or 1990s, especially in the U.S.; a member of Generation Y.

murderous.Name: murderous
murderous.Description: guilty of, bent on, or capable of murder.

pro-gun.Name: pro-gun
pro-gun.Description: relating to or supporting the elimination or reduction of limits and regulations on the sale and use of firearms.

slightly-faster-than-normal.Name: slightly-faster-than-normal
slightly-faster-than-normal.Description: someone who is slightly faster than the average person, in both running speed and reflexes.

theological.Name: theological
theological.Description: based upon the nature and will of God as revealed to humans.

transcended.Name: transcended
transcended.Description: going beyond ordinary limits; surpassing; exceeding.

unparalled.Name: unparalled
unparalled.Description: not paralleled; unequaled or unmatched; peerless; unprecedented.

wise.Name: wise
wise.Description: having the power of discerning and judging properly as to what is true or right; possessing discernment, judgment, or discretion.

worldwide.Name: worldwide
worldwide.Description: extending or spread throughout the world.

young.Name: young
young.Description: being in the first or early stage of life or growth; youthful; not old.

zealous.Name: zealous
zealous.Description: full of, characterized by, or due to zeal; ardently active, devoted, or diligent.

zoomer.Name: zoomer
zoomer.Description: Zoomer is a nickname referring to members of Generation Z, those born in the late 90s and early 2000s. Its use is particularly popular as a contrast to baby boomer or boomer, but before Gen Z was established, zoomer was used to refer to especially active baby boomers.
